text: Frankenstein (Sachs) station is a railway station in Oberschöna, Saxony, Germany. It is named after Frankenstein, which was the nearest settlement when the railway line was built and the station opened. ==References== ==External links== Category:Railway stations in Saxony Category:Buildings and structures in Mittelsachsen Category:Railway stations in Germany opened in 1869
title: Frankenstein (Sachs) station
